## Cohort Discovery: fix cross-namespace predicate — local-name alias fallback

Context: After the first fix, `ElectricitySuspended` still returned nothing.
Investigation revealed a second, deeper bug: the domain's object property URIs
use `https://ontobricks.com/ontology#hasclaim` (an inherited shared namespace)
while the domain's `base_uri` is `https://databricks-ontology.com/Cust360Auto#`
and the triplestore predicates are `https://databricks-ontology.com/Cust360Auto/hasclaim`.
`_to_data_uri` can only bridge `#` ↔ `/` within the **same** base namespace;
it cannot cross two completely unrelated namespaces. The same issue is already
solved by `SparqlTranslator` via local-name matching — `CohortBuilder` needed
the same treatment.

### Changes

1. `src/back/core/graph_analysis/CohortBuilder.py`
   - Added `_predicate_alias_map()` — scans loaded triples and builds
     `{local_name → canonical_data_namespace_uri}`. Cached in
     `self._cache["predicate_alias"]` and invalidated on triple reload.
   - Added `_resolve_predicate(uri)` — calls `_to_data_uri` first; if the
     URI is unchanged (foreign namespace), falls back to the alias map by
     local name. This is the mirror of `SparqlTranslator._predicate_local_name_key`.
   - Updated `_normalized_links` to use `_resolve_predicate` instead of
     `_to_data_uri` for hop `via` and `where[*].property`.
   - Updated `_normalized_compat` to use `_resolve_predicate` for
     `compatibility[*].property`.

2. `tests/test_cohort_builder.py`
   - Added `test_via_from_foreign_namespace_resolved_by_local_name` — exact
     replica of the production scenario (domain base `…/Cust360Auto#`,
     property URIs `https://ontobricks.com/ontology#hasclaim`, data triples
     `…/Cust360Auto/hasclaim`) that proves the fix end-to-end.

### Modified files

- `src/back/core/graph_analysis/CohortBuilder.py`
- `tests/test_cohort_builder.py`

