## Cohort Discovery: restrict attribute dropdown to entity's own properties

Context: In the Path "where" filter and the Compatibility section, the property
dropdown listed every property in the ontology regardless of the entity being
filtered. Users had to scroll through unrelated properties (e.g. Agent properties
when filtering a Claim hop). The same issue applied to the root-entity compatibility
section.

### Changes

1. `src/front/static/query/js/query-cohorts.js`
   - Added `_dataPropsForClass(classUri)` helper — mirrors the existing
     `_objectPropsForSource` pattern: filters to data properties (non-object)
     whose `domain` matches the class name; falls back to all data properties
     if nothing matches.
   - `_renderHopWhereRow`: replaced raw `this.properties` with
     `_dataPropsForClass(targetClassUri)` so each hop's filter shows only
     the target entity's own attributes.
   - `_renderCompat`: replaced raw `this.properties` with
     `_dataPropsForClass(this.rule.class_uri)` so the compatibility section
     shows only the root entity's attributes.

### Modified files

- `src/front/static/query/js/query-cohorts.js`

### Test results

```
tests/test_cohort_builder.py  49 passed
```
